# Giới Thiệu -- Introduction
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Giới Thiệu"

msgid "An Armature in Blender can be thought of as similar to the armature of a real skeleton, and just like a real skeleton an Armature can consist of many bones. These bones can be moved around and anything that they are attached to or associated with will move and deform in a similar way."
msgstr "An Armature in Blender can be thought of as similar to the armature of a real skeleton, and just like a real skeleton an Armature can consist of many bones. These bones can be moved around and anything that they are attached to or associated with will move and deform in a similar way."

# An "armature" is a type of object used for rigging. A rig is the controls and strings that move a marionette (puppet). Armature object borrows many ideas from real-world skeletons.
msgid "An \"armature\" is a type of object used for rigging. A rig is the controls and strings that move a marionette (puppet). Armature object borrows many ideas from real-world skeletons."
msgstr "An \"armature\" is a type of object used for :doc:`rigging </rigging/index>`. A rig is the controls and strings that move a marionette (puppet). Armature object borrows many ideas from real-world skeletons."

msgid "Your First Armature"
msgstr "Your First Armature"

msgid "In order to see what we are talking about, let us try to add the default armature in Blender."
msgstr "In order to see what we are talking about, let us try to add the default armature in Blender."

# (Note that armature editing details are explained in the :doc:`armatures editing section </animation/armatures/bones/editing/index>`.)
msgid "(Note that armature editing details are explained in the :doc:`armatures editing section </animation/armatures/bones/editing/index>`.)"
msgstr "(Note that armature editing details are explained in the :doc:`armatures editing section </rigging/armatures/bones/editing/index>`)."

msgid "Open a default scene, then:"
msgstr "Open a default scene, then:"

msgid "Delete all objects in the scene."
msgstr "Delete all objects in the scene."

msgid "Make sure the cursor is in the world origin with :kbd:`Shift-C`."
msgstr "Make sure the cursor is in the world origin with :kbd:`:kbd:`Shift-C``."

msgid "Press :kbd:`Numpad1` to see the world in Front view."
msgstr "Press :kbd:`:kbd:`Số 1 Bàn Số (Numpad1)`` to see the world in Front view."

# Add a *Xương Đơn -- Single Bone* (:menuselection:`Add --> Armature`).
msgid "Add a *Single Bone* (:menuselection:`Add --> Armature`)."
msgstr "Add a *Single Bone* (:menuselection:`Cộng Thêm (Add) --> Cốt (Armature) --> Đơn Xương (Single Bone)`)."

msgid "Press :kbd:`NumpadDelete` to see the armature at maximum zoom."
msgstr "Press :kbd:`:kbd:`Dấu Xóa/Del Bàn Số (NumpadDelete)`` to see the armature at maximum zoom."

msgid "The default armature."
msgstr "The default armature."

msgid "The Armature Object"
msgstr "The Armature Object"

msgid "As you can see, an armature is like any other object type in Blender:"
msgstr "As you can see, an armature is like any other object type in Blender:"

msgid "It has an origin, a position, a rotation and a scale factor."
msgstr "It has an origin, a position, a rotation and a scale factor."

msgid "It has an Object Data data-block, that can be edited in *Edit Mode*."
msgstr "It has an Object Data data-block, that can be edited in *Chế Độ Biên Soạn -- Edit Mode*."

msgid "It can be linked to other scenes, and the same armature data can be reused on multiple objects."
msgstr "It can be linked to other scenes, and the same armature data can be reused on multiple objects."

msgid "All animation you do in *Object Mode* is only working on the whole object, not the armature's bones (use the *Pose Mode* to do this)."
msgstr "All animation you do in *Chế Độ Vật Thể -- Object Mode* is only working on the whole object, not the armature's bones (use the *Chế Độ Tư Thế -- Pose Mode* to do this)."

msgid "As armatures are designed to be posed, either for a static or animated scene, they have a specific state, called \"rest position\". This is the armature's default \"shape\", the default position/rotation/scale of its bones, as set in *Edit Mode*."
msgstr "As armatures are designed to be posed, either for a static or animated scene, they have a specific state, called \"rest position\". This is the armature's default \"shape\", the default position/rotation/scale of its bones, as set in *Chế Độ Biên Soạn -- Edit Mode*."

msgid "In *Edit Mode*, you will always see your armature in rest position, whereas in *Object Mode* and *Pose Mode*, you usually get the current \"pose\" of the armature (unless you enable the *Rest Position* button of the *Armature* panel)."
msgstr "In *Chế Độ Biên Soạn -- Edit Mode*, you will always see your armature in rest position, whereas in *Chế Độ Vật Thể -- Object Mode* and *Chế Độ Tư Thế -- Pose Mode*, you usually get the current \"pose\" of the armature (unless you enable the *Tư Thế Nghỉ -- Rest Position* button of the *Cốt -- Armature* panel)."

